## Early game

**Cervantes** on Earth (Sabotage) has a reliably documented Detonite Ampule
source: a Rotation B resource cache with roughly a 12.2% chance. That cache is
a reward table rather than an enemy drop, so a booster and the Steel Path
passive don't affect it — but as a quick, guaranteed-structure Sabotage
(clear the tileset, grab the Rotation B cache, reset) it's the clearest early
source. For a boosted enemy farm, see the endgame spot below.

## Mid & late game

**Piscinas** on Saturn (Dark Sector Survival) is the wiki's recommended
endgame spot, run with a Steel Path squad. Detonite Ampule is in Saturn's
region resource pool, so it drops from the Grineer you kill — meaning a
Resource Drop Booster, the Steel Path passive and a Nekros loot squad all
stack here, and long Survival rotations pile up kills for the biggest hauls.

